==English==

===Etymology===
Late 18th century, from Greek: ''eúdio(s)'' 'clear, fine', from ''eu'' 'well' + ''dios'' 'heavenly'

===Noun===
{{en-noun}}

# A [[graduated]] [[glass]] [[tube]], closed at one end, that is used for measuring the change in the [[volume]] of [[gas]]es during a [[chemical reaction]].

